-- China Coal Mine Flood Kills y Miners, People’s Daily Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-05-02T16:34:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/china-coal-mine-flooding-traps-at-least-10-miners-xinhua-says.html
Seven miners died and seven remain
trapped after a coal-mine flood in northeastern  China ’s
Heilongjiang province yesterday, the official Xinhua News Agency
reported, citing unidentified rescuers.  A total of 14 miners escaped or were rescued, Xinhua said.
A total of 28 workers were underground when the accident
happened at 7 a.m. local time at the Junyuan coal pit in Hegang
city, Xinhua said. The mine was licensed, it said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
